  <rules>
    <rule id="http://bentoweb.org/refs/rulesets.xml#WCAG2_20050630_3.1_meaning-located" primary="yes">
      <locations expectedResult="pass">
        <location line="9" column="34" xpath="/:html/:body/:p/:span" />
      </locations>
      <functionalOutcome>
        <p>The user can find the expanded forms of abbreviatons and/or acronyms.</p>
      </functionalOutcome>
      <techComment>
        <p>This test case is the same as xhtml1_wcag2_20050630_3.1_l3_sc3_002, but the order of the acronym and the expanded form is reversed.
            The 23 November 2005 version of "Understanding <html:acronym>WCAG</html:acronym> 2.0 lists "providing the abbreviation immediately following the first use of the expanded form within the delivery unit"
            as a "sufficient technique".
            See http://www.w3.org/TR/2005/WD-UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20-20051123/#meaning-located.
          </p>
      </techComment>
    </rule>
  </rules>
